      "body" : "This is still happening with master, on mainnet, as of last week (with #9128 merged), or came back with one of the pulls I was testing, see #9348.\r\n\r\nNit: we should avoid using assert() for error handling in network code. We should just log a message in these cases and boot the peer. It's only a small step from a bug/oversight to a P2P-triggerable DoS.",
